
----------------------------------

# pipenv : combination of pip and virtualenv, ie; creates a virtualenv as well as install the required package.
  -> installation : pip3 install pipenv / pip3 install --user pipenv
  -> Usage:
     first create a directory and then inside that dir run the following command.
     $pipenv install <package_name> 

     $cd <myEnv>
     $pipenv --python 3.6 : creates a virtualenv with particular python version

Creates following files after creating virtualenv:

  Pipfile : replacements of requirements.txt
  Pipfile.lock : contians versions of packages

$pipenv --where : tells path where it is installed
$pipenv --venv : tells path of virtualenv created
$pipenv

# Running the program in virtualenv
   $pipenv run python filename.py


$pipenv graph : lists the packages with their dependencies.

   $pipenv shell : Activating the env
   (env)$deactivate/exit : deactive the env

$pipenv check : check updates

$pipenv install -r requirements.txt : create virtualenv with specified packages in requirements.txt

